Designed and implemented a scalable wired network for ABC Pte Ltd, a mock IT solutions company, to support anticipated growth. The proposed network, implemented using Cisco Packet Tracer, includes using VLSM for efficient IP address allocation, OSPF as the routing protocol, HSRP for redundancy and configuration of PCs, switches, and routers with appropriate addresses and settings. The logical network diagram serves as a foundational blueprint, ensuring robust and future-proof infrastructure capable of handling the company's expansion needs.
Grade: A
